      "inheritance_hierarchy": "EURFToken inherits ERC20MetaTxUpgradeable (ERC20Upgradeable+EIP712Upgradeable), ERC20AdminUpgradeable (ERC20Upgradeable+PausableUpgradeable+AccessControlEnumerableUpgradeable), ERC20ControlerMinterUpgradeable (ERC20Upgradeable+AccessControlEnumerableUpgradeable), FeesHandlerUpgradeable (Initializable), and UUPSUpgradeable. Both ERC20AdminUpgradeable and ERC20ControlerMinterUpgradeable also inherit AccessControlEnumerableUpgradeable, creating a multi-inheritance composition over shared AccessControl and ERC20 state via OZ upgradeable base classes.",
      "external_dependencies": [
        "OpenZeppelin upgradeable: UUPSUpgradeable, Initializable, ContextUpgradeable, ERC20Upgradeable, PausableUpgradeable, AccessControlEnumerableUpgradeable, EIP712Upgradeable, OwnableUpgradeable",
        "OpenZeppelin (non-upgradeable): ECDSA"
      ],
      "upgrade_patterns": "UUPS proxy pattern for EURFToken (implementation contract inherits UUPSUpgradeable; upgrades authorized by OWNER role via _authorizeUpgrade). Forwarder is upgradeable (OwnableUpgradeable + initializer) but no proxy contract is shown here; if proxied, it relies on Initializable guards in initialize().",
      "access_control_structure": "EURFToken uses AccessControlEnumerable roles. OWNER is aliased to DEFAULT_ADMIN_ROLE. ADMIN is a separate role used for operational admin actions. MASTER_MINTER is intended as admin of MINTER_ROLE (via _setRoleAdmin). CONTROLLER is a separate role used solely for safetySwitch toggling. Forwarder uses OwnableUpgradeable for admin-only request type registration. Note: multiple external functions in ERC20ControlerMinterUpgradeable (addController/removeController/addMinter/removeMinter/setMasterMinter) lack explicit access modifiers and rely on inherited AccessControl's grantRole/revokeRole authorization behavior (which itself restricts to role admin), but these functions are still public entry points."
    },
